§1 — YOU ARE FREE TO

  - Use SnowFoxOS for any personal or commercial purpose
  - Study how it works — the code is always open
  - Share it with anyone, as long as this license stays with it
  - Build upon it and make it your own


§2 — YOU MUST

  - Always credit the original author: Xr7-Code
  - Keep this license file intact and visible
  - Make any modifications publicly available under this
    same license — you cannot close what was open
  - Clearly state what you changed if you distribute
    a modified version


§3 — YOU MUST NOT

  - Claim SnowFoxOS or any derivative as solely your own work
  - Sell SnowFoxOS or a derivative without explicit written
    permission from the original author
  - Add telemetry, tracking, analytics, or any form of
    surveillance to any derivative
  - Use this project or its name to mislead, manipulate,
    or harm its users in any way
  - Strip or weaken the privacy or freedom features of
    any derivative and present it as SnowFoxOS


§4 — THE SPIRIT OF THIS LICENSE

  This project was built on a simple belief:

  Your computer belongs to you.
  Your data belongs to you.
  Your freedom belongs to you.

  Any derivative of SnowFoxOS must honor this belief.
  A version of SnowFoxOS that tracks its users,
  sells their data, or treats them as a product
  is not SnowFoxOS — it is its opposite.

  The name "SnowFoxOS" may only be used for distributions
  that fully respect the user's freedom and privacy.


§5 — THE HUMAN CLAUSE

  This software recognizes that behind every screen
  is a person — not a user, not a data point, not a product.

  Any version of this software, modified or unmodified,
  must never be used to harm, manipulate, surveil,
  or exploit the people who use it.

  People are not replaceable.
  People deserve to be happy.
  This software exists to serve them — not the other way around.


§6 — DISCLAIMER

  This software is provided as-is, without warranty of any kind.
  The author is not responsible for damages arising from its use.
  You use it freely, and you use it at your own risk.


